      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the very spark of my soul. He is gone, and with him, the last shred of reason I held dear. Every shadow in this wretched room seems to whisper of my inadequacy, of a life lived only to be discarded like a wilted rose. I find myself longing for the quiet dark... to simply dissolve into the mist and never wake to this hollow ache again. Is there no mercy in this cruel world but the silence of the grave?",
